Next week on March 8 I will be teaching a one day online workshop “Wipe Out Technique”. This method is much faster and more fluid than a traditional monochrome Underpainting and is useful for any kind of subject matter.

I use this technique frequently to quickly assess the effectiveness of a compositional idea.  My students have had great success with it as well.  If you can’t make the live session, the class is fully recorded in HD and available for unlimited viewing.  I hope you can join me!  The link for information is in my bio.

Every painting begins with large masses of color
#oilpainting #realistpainting #color #flowers #flowerpainting

I think I just had a major insight into what my subjects really are. 

They are not objects in a still life or even figures. They are portals into a world that exists all around us in nature. They do not speak human language and I feel that it is my job to translate their presence. 

For  years I have felt a sense of dissatisfaction with many of my paintings. In trying to force the subjects into a “genre” they lose their originality, their specific voice.  From now on I am going to let them take the lead in the dance.  We will see what happens.

Please join me for an upcoming Livestream on May 24! 
This will be sponsored by Workshops in Yorkshire associated with Rosemary Brushes

I’ll be choosing a subject from the wonderful Rose Garden on the estate and doing a 3 hour demonstration of my process. 

The Livestream is fully recorded and available for two years so no worries if you can’t make the live class time. 

Rose season is upon us and I’d love to share my crazy enthusiasm for the subject with you! 
The link to register is in my bio 

#workshopsinyorkshire  #livestream #roses #rosepainting #oilpainting #paintingdemo

Upcoming Fall Still Life Workshop!

( Live on Zoom. Classes are fully recorded in HD if you cannot attend the live session)

The forms and colors of Fall are simply exquisite.  I will be using beautiful models from a local apple orchard.

The process of painting still life is inherently meditative. The slow revelation of form through light and color can be a deeply satisfying experience. For the class, you may choose images from a group I have prepared--all pretty gorgeous, if I do say so myself--or create a set up of your own. The link for more information and enrollment is in my bio. 

See you soon, I hope!

One-Day Workshop
I have a new Drawing Class coming up in February! 
Link for more info is in my profile 

Basic Botanical Structure Drawing
Wednesday, February 7, 10 am - 1 pm, EST 
$100

Drawing is the backbone of painting and a fundamental first step in the investigation of botanical form.

Flowers, along with their stems and leaves, are intricate pieces of living architecture. To paint them effectively, you need to grasp the way that they grow along with their three-dimensional presence in space. 

In this one-day workshop, Kathy will demonstrate the method of structural drawing she uses to study flowers before exploring them in her paintings. She thinks of them as figures with all the complexity we find in the human form.

This inspiring subject can prove quite intimidating. Kathy's workshop will give you a meditative, low-pressure way to "know" your subject before tackling it in the more complex language of oil painting. 

If you have never drawn flowers before, this is the class for you!  If you have experience with the subject, it will refresh your skills.

Suitable for beginning to advanced students.

#drawing #drawingclasses #botanical #botanicalart #basicdrawing #flowerdrawing
